239
00:19:09,610 --> 00:19:12,440
I-It was a slip of the tongue.

240
00:19:13,610 --> 00:19:15,970
I'm terribly sorry.

241
00:19:15,970 --> 00:19:20,650
You come to my home,
and meddle in my family's business?

242
00:19:20,650 --> 00:19:26,700
Who taught you manners?
Did you even attend school?

243
00:19:28,670 --> 00:19:30,720
Answer me.

244
00:19:31,780 --> 00:19:34,840
Are you a mere high school graduate?

245
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:40,800
You must have attended a no-name school.

246
00:19:41,860 --> 00:19:46,720
I suppose that's no surprise,
given you're only a photographer.

247
00:19:47,510 --> 00:19:53,300
And now you've come here,
judging me for my own choices?

248
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:57,580
Oh how I'd love to see your parents.

249
00:19:59,310 --> 00:20:03,880
They must not be very cultured themselves.

250
00:20:10,840 --> 00:20:16,100
Mother. Sakuraba is a skilled photographer.

251
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:23,150
His work impressed you too, did they not?

252
00:20:24,390 --> 00:20:27,430
Forgive me for speaking out of turn,

253
00:20:27,430 --> 00:20:33,200
but you cannot judge a person
based on their education or career.

254
00:20:34,770 --> 00:20:37,220
Sakuraba's photos are first class.

255
00:20:37,220 --> 00:20:40,790
I will not allow you
to speak down on his work.

256
00:20:40,790 --> 00:20:42,720
His education doesn't matter.

257
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:45,340
I trust him.

258
00:20:46,900 --> 00:20:49,980
I'm the one who asked for his help.

259
00:20:49,980 --> 00:20:56,250
He feels responsible, as another party
who was at the scene of the incident.

